I agree with Dreks.  I had the same idea.  If you put on your LFG flag, people should be able to see your level.  Maybe your class too.<br>
<br>
The only thing I would add to this is that I should be able to see all of the levels and classes of my fellow guild members.<br>
<br>
Language is only a problem if you let it be a problem.  If you take one hour and practice a language with someone (spam, zone, rinse and repeat)  you will have no problem conversing with someone.<br>
<br>
TLC is only a problem (for lower level quests) if you let it be a problem.  If I need a low level quest item because I didn't get it the first time around, I would create a PC quest with the goal being a bounty for the quest item.  For example, if I need to get Master Whoopall's head, I can create a bounty for the first person willing to go and separate Whoopall's head from his shoulders.  The other player gets cash or an item and I get the head.  I have a feeling this scenario is the basis for removing NO DROP on most items on FV.<br>
<br>
I have had a few characters on other servers.  FV is by far the best server.  The d00ds don't stick around here because the ruleset isn't &quot;easy&quot;.  Good, let'em go.  Create a character on another server and go sit in EC for ten minutes and you'll camp out and come back to FV.<br>
<br>
