Sexy. Tall. Green. Deadly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeffhead01.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deffhead01</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Gnevil Mastermind</span><br>  Posts: 98<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 5:49:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> Although you did not write it specifically, one could get the notion that you felt that, those that left the server was the so called &quot;d00dz&quot; first and foremost.<br>
I think it would be very wrong to believe that those that leave are mostly &quot;d00dz&quot;. <br>
Actually, I think there are players of all kinds that leave the FV server, but mostly, I would imagine most of those are casual players. With the current rules in place, it makes it close to impossible for the casual player, if he or she is not in a big guild that is around when he/she is, or if he/she brings her own group when starting on the server.<br>
<br>
A damn shame if you ask me, since as most of you have already found out, FV is a server with a high percentage of mature and nice (role)players.<br>
<br>
(By the way, I am one of those people that started at day 1, but left after reaching level 20, due to the current rules. I am still lurking on the boards, though, since I hope the situation will improve one day, so I can re-activate my account.) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uimogenelddar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ImogenElddar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 6:15:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is dying... slowly but surely</span><hr size=1> &lt;&lt;IMHO, if FV was turned into a normal blue server, we wouldn't see a huge inrush of &quot;farming d00ds&quot;. &gt;&gt;<br>
<br>
I do wish you were right, but I fear that you aren't.<br>
<br>
If and when Verant does feel that this server is &quot;dying&quot; (and their idea of dying will probably be &quot;unprofitable&quot;), I'm sure that they will do something.  My guess is, they will take a single step towards making FV a normal server.  In other words, I predict that FV will drop ONE of the rules.  Probably either TLC or forced /role.  <br>
<br>
Verant won't admit that they are doing it out of desperation, either.  They will claim (with some honesty) that they are doing what they were asked to do by the players. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 80<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 6:53:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The server is *NOT* dying... slowly *OR* surely</span><hr size=1> I agree with Valquiss.  I don't believe the &quot;server is dying&quot;.  I'm not at all sure how you'd evaluate that, anyway.<br>
<br>
There are throngs of people in Kelethin all the time now, and the number is pretty much the same stable number it was when I first started in October: about 60-70 during the weekends, about 40 on weekdays, about 20 at night.<br>
<br>
What is different, however, are the hordes of people in the low-to-mid-level dungeons.  Crushbone regularly has 20-30 people in it--it only has fewer if someone's trained DVinn to the zone and he's slaughtered everyone.<br>
<br>
When I spent time in Blackburrow, there were generally more people running around than gnolls except very, very late at night.<br>
<br>
I don't think &quot;the server is dying&quot;.  I think people are levelling slowly, like myself, partly in order not to miss out on quests that otherwise might TLC.  Or because they're &quot;casual gamers&quot;, like myself.<br>
<br>
I suspect that, to people in their 40s, yeah, it looks like the server is dead because there are very few people up there, relatively speaking.  However, the wave is coming.  The people in Crushbone/Blackburrow/etc now will be moving into their 20s soon, and there are a lot of them.<br>
<br>
Also, Sullon Zek hasn't been shut down.  I don't think there is, as of yet, any precendence that indicates VI will shut either server down.  They fit a &quot;niche-market&quot; that VI wants to attract--after all, how many people here have said they'd completely quit the game if it weren't for FV?<br>
<br>
Lasgalen, Nineteenth Autumn Initiate of Tunare (finally) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 229<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/20/02 8:06:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You can't ..</span><hr size=1> .. judge it from G.Fay.  That's the only zone in the game with both a portal and /auction.  It will *always* be a gathering spot no matter how low the server population gets.<br>
<br>
We definitely loose a lot of players.  Personally, I think there are only two rules that actually make even a token effort at supporting RP: the language changes and the alignments.  Both have very poor implementations, though.  The entire ruleset simply ammounts to an extra hurdle.  If you're an experienced player, you can probably overcome it -- or at least you won't quit too early, since you know what you're up against from the start.<br>
<br>
Examples:<br>
<br>
TLC -- not RP.  Just makes quests *extremely* difficult or even impossible if you don't read the spoiler sites.<br>
<br>
/roleplay -- not RP.  It means I have to ask and am asked class/level constantly.  I'd prefer conversations to not require game mechanics in the first hello.<br>
<br>
No /ooc or /auc, /yell-range /auc and /shout -- not RP.  RP is handled entirely through communication.  Limitted communication means limitted RP (and you can always turn off /occ, /auc, or /shout if they bother you).<br>
<br>
Languages -- RP on one side, communication limitting on the other.  Should have been done just with NPCs, not PCs.<br>
<br>
Alignment -- RP, but with bad implemenation that limits player creativity.  Should have been done wide open, but with faction consequences; eg. inky can go &quot;good&quot;, but if he does, Neriak/etc. become KoS.<br>
<br>
I could go on and on about how the ruleset really doesn't do anything but make things harder.  It doesn't support RP because Verant never defined what RP was when they went out to support it.  They seem to have just added a bunch of odd restrictions to force folks into small narrow niches.  RP is about creativity and your own storyline, not about marching in step with the NPCs. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 2:06:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: You can't ..</span><hr size=1> I'm not judging &quot;just by Greater Faydark.&quot;<br>
<br>
I'm judging by the increasing horde of people I've seen in Crushbone and in Blackburrow on a regular basis.<br>
<br>
I'm judging by my experiences in Highpass, where there's almost always two full groups, one on either end.<br>
<br>
I'm judging by my experiences in the East Commonlands, where there were 20-some people there at 3:00 a.m. my time last night.<br>
<br>
Yes, some of zones have fewer people than others, but I think patience will reveal that the server is thriving, in spite of what the doomsayers think (or desire).<br>
<br>
Lastly, if you hate all the server's rules, go back to your blue server.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen, Nineteenth Autumn Initiate of Tunare<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 2:44:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> You're judging by ..</span><hr size=1> .. all the easy lowbie zones.  People quit *after* those zones.  With all the loot fights you get into, Robin, I'm surprised you ever get a group.  Guess not all read these boards, eh? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umellandra.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mellandra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/21/02 4:34:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1151.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> SoL</span><hr size=1> Personally, I think that the population of the server is much less because of the amount of people that can't run EQ any more because after the Shadows of Luclin update their computers aren't up to scratch any more.  I think FV has taken a bit of a blow (like all the servers will have done) but should hopefully now be on the rise. <p><p>
