a) People that joined this server for a challenge (They want to become uber first, not roleplay)<br>
b) Farmers who thought they could get rich because of lower population<br>
c) d00ds who like showing off their uber gear, but can not shout about how uber they are because the language and limited shout range<br>
d) People whose computers could not handle the Luclin expansion (We have had a number of these in our guild)<br>
<br>
     I believe this server is doing well for the people it was designed for. People who like to roleplay, casual gamers who dislike the crowds and want to see the sights that are always camped on other servers and older players who can never understand d00ds. Now this does not mean RP at all times, but as a matter of practice.<br>
     I do see a problem with the 40+ group though. They all leveled so fast that a gap formed between them and the rest of the server. Alot of them came with ready formed guilds and power leveled their way to the top. Then when FV did not meet their expectations they left and there is not enough mid-level people to fill their shoes.<br>
     My guild, which started about week 3 of this server, is doing well with our leadership group in the mid 20's, even more teens and a few in their 30's. We are growing at a slow and measured pace like we want to keep that family atmosphere. There is almost always someone to group with in our level ranges, but it is rarely over-camped which is nice. Sometimes it can seem there is not enough people in your range because alot of people are busy running quests and things instead of grouping. This has happened to me before where I run a quest one night and the next a person I usually group with is doing the same.<br>
     I like the closeness of this server, the slower pace and the feeling that you know most of the people around you. I always know some of the people I run past on the way from FP to Qeynos, on my old server I never did. Leave the server the way it is. I see it as a fine wine, it will just get better as it ages.<br>
<br>
Lexxi Ledenyetz<br>
25th Prayer<br>
Cleric of Brell<br>
Ak'Anon<br>
Officer and Heiress - Ledenyetz Troupe<br>
